ros formation is essential for autophagy
the results described above suggest that starvation induces
ros formation. but are ros essential for autophagy? to
address this question, we tested the effect of n-acetyl-l-
cysteine (nac), a general antioxidant, and catalase, which
speciﬁcally decomposes h2o2, on the formation of autopha-
gosomes using gate-16 and lc3 as markers. lc3 and gate-
16 were shown to label autophagosomes under starvation
conditions (kabeya et al, 2004; supplementary figure 3a),
and as shown in supplementary figure 3b, the two proteins
